Miami Gardens is situated within the [United States](/List_of_sovereign_states), specifically in the [State](/U.S._state) of [Florida](/Florida), residing within [Miami-Dade County](/Miami-Dade_County,_Florida). This municipality officially achieved [incorporation](/Municipal_corporation) on May 13, 2003, marking its formal establishment a mere 22 years ago (2003-05-13).

### Government

The governance structure of Miami Gardens operates under a [Council-Manager](/Council-manager_government) system, a common enough arrangement designed to separate policy-making from administrative execution. The current [Mayor](/Mayor) presiding over this council is Rodney Harris, while Katrina Wilson holds the position of [Vice Mayor](/Vice_Mayor). The legislative body, the [City Council](/City_Council), comprises several members: Shannon Campbell, Reggie Leon, Shannan Ighodaro, Linda Julien, and Robert L. Stephens III. Day-to-day administrative affairs are handled by the [City Manager](/City_Manager), Cameron Benson, with Mario Bataille serving as the [City Clerk](/City_Clerk). One might wonder how many layers of bureaucracy it takes to simply keep the lights on.

### Area

According to official measurements, the total area of the [city](/List_of_communities_in_Miami-Dade_County,_Florida) spans approximately 19.00 square miles (49.21 square kilometers). Of this, a substantial 18.23 square miles (47.21 square kilometers) constitutes land area, leaving a rather modest 0.77 square miles (2.00 square kilometers) as water. This gives one a clear picture of where the actual living and working takes place.

### Elevation

The city rests at a relatively low [elevation](/Elevation), approximately 6.6 feet (2 meters) above sea level. In a state like Florida, this detail is rarely comforting.

### Population

As of the [2020 United States census](/2020_United_States_census), the recorded [population](/List_of_communities_in_Miami-Dade_County,_Florida) of Miami Gardens stood at 111,640 individuals. This translates to a population [density](/Density) of roughly 6,125 residents per square mile (or 2,365 per square kilometer). The broader [Miami metropolitan area](/Metropolitan_area), of which Miami Gardens is a part, encompasses a significantly larger population of 5,564,635 people.

### Time Zone

Miami Gardens observes the [Eastern Time Zone](/Eastern_Time_Zone), operating under [UTC−5](/UTC%E2%88%925) (EST). During the summer months, with the implementation of [Daylight Saving Time](/Daylight_saving_time) (DST), the time shifts to [UTC−4](/UTC%E2%88%924) (EDT). A minor adjustment in the grand scheme of things, but important for those who still adhere to such temporal constructs.

