## Surrounding areas

Miami Gardens does not exist in isolation, but rather as a node within a larger geographical network. Its immediate neighbors delineate its place in the south Florida landscape.

*   To the north, Miami Gardens shares a boundary with [Broward County](/Broward_County,_Florida), specifically the city of [Miramar](/Miramar,_Florida).
*   Further along its northern edge, the city's reach extends to meet both [Miramar](/Miramar,_Florida) and [West Park](/West_Park,_Florida), both also situated within [Broward County](/Broward_County,_Florida).
*   To its immediate west, the city interfaces with [Country Club](/Country_Club,_Florida) and [Miami Lakes](/Miami_Lakes,_Florida). Proceeding eastward along this latitude, it borders [Ives Estates](/Ives_Estates,_Florida), [Ojus](/Ojus,_Florida), [North Miami Beach](/North_Miami_Beach,_Florida), and various [unincorporated areas](/Unincorporated_area) of [Miami-Dade County](/Miami-Dade_County,_Florida).
*   Directly to the west, another segment of [Miami Lakes](/Miami_Lakes,_Florida) marks its boundary, alongside additional [unincorporated areas](/Unincorporated_area) of [Miami-Dade County](/Miami-Dade_County,_Florida).
*   To its south, Miami Gardens borders further [unincorporated areas](/Unincorporated_area) of [Miami-Dade County](/Miami-Dade_County,_Florida) and [North Miami Beach](/North_Miami_Beach,_Florida).